2.1/ A rational agent acts to maximize its expected performance measure. If that measure is only concerned about the T time steps and ignores everything after, the value of certain actions changes as the clock ticks closer to that deadline. Let\'92s suppose a vacuum agent gets +10 points for cleaning a room but -1 point for every move, and cleaning takes 2 moves. Then if the agent is at time T-1 moving to clean is irrational, as he would have time for 1 move and just lose 1 point. Therefore his optimal action in the exact same state would be to stay still at time T-1 but to move at time T-3\
